content:
You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Service Cloud > Customize Call Routing

Customize call routing by defining rules for where voice calls go. By default, calls route to the SCV Basic Queue using the Default for Voice configuration. 

Route Calls to Queues
Use Omni-Channel to route calls to specific queues or agents.

Alternatively, create an Omni-Channel flow to define more complex routing rules and dynamically route calls.

This feature is available with Service Cloud Voice and Amazon Connect, or other Partner Telephony models.

Route Calls with Omni-Channel Flows
Build a template-based flow in Flow Builder to assign voice calls to the right agent or queue.
title: Customizing Call Routing in Service Cloud
